==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: big bang
<hw>big bang</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>The explosive
event marking the beginning of the known universe, according to <er>big
bang theory</er>; the beginning of time.</def> <note>The <ex>big
bang</ex> is likened to a massive explosion from a point containing all
of the matter and energy of the beginning universe, which started the
expansion and evolution of the universe which continues today. The
evidence for such an event includes the apparently expanding size of the
present universe, and a background microwave radiation of about 3⟦deg⟧
Kelvin, equal to that predicted from mathematical models of such an
explosive event.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>big bang theory</ent>⟦br⟧
